<section class="flex-auto flex flex-column flex-row-ns bg-white black-70">
  <div class="fl w-100 w-100-ns pa2">
    <h3 class="f6 ttu tracked mt0">Styleguide</h3>
    <p class="measure f5 lh-copy sans-serif">Welcome to the Healthlocker styleguide. This is where we document the components that make up the Healthlocker application.</p>
    <p class="measure f5 lh-copy sans-serif">If you're looking to build any front-end pages look here for which components to use, and then use the corresponding helper or partial to correctly generate the markup (with Tachyons classes).</p>

    <div class="bg-white pv4">
      <h2 class="f3">Color Palette</h1>
      <p class="f5 lh-copy sans-serif">The naming convention for color classes: <code>.hl-dark-blue</code> or <code>.hl-bg-terracotta</code> (for background colours)</p>
      <ul class="list pl0 ml0 cf">
        <li class="fl w-100 w-50-m w-25-l mb1">
          <div class="fl w-40 pv4 hl-bg-grey"></div>
          <div class="fl w-60 lh-copy pl2 pt2">
            <b class="db">grey</b>
            <code class="f6">#EBEBEB</code>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="fl w-100 w-50-m w-25-l mb1">
          <div class="fl w-40 pv4 hl-bg-dark-blue"></div>
          <div class="fl w-60 lh-copy pl2 pt2">
            <b class="db">dark blue</b>
            <code class="f6">#242F4F</code>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="fl w-100 w-50-m w-25-l mb1">
          <div class="fl w-40 pv4 hl-bg-dark-grey"></div>
          <div class="fl w-60 lh-copy pl2 pt2">
            <b class="db">dark grey</b>
            <code class="f6">#242F4F</code>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="fl w-100 w-50-m w-25-l mb1">
          <div class="fl w-40 pv4 hl-bg-pink"></div>
          <div class="fl w-60 lh-copy pl2 pt2">
            <b class="db">pink</b>
            <code class="f6">#EC4067</code>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="fl w-100 w-50-m w-25-l mb1">
          <div class="fl w-40 pv4 bg-white"></div>
          <div class="fl w-60 lh-copy pl2 pt2">
            <b class="db">white</b>
            <code class="f6">#FFFFFF</code>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="fl w-100 w-50-m w-25-l mb1">
          <div class="fl w-40 pv4 hl-bg-aqua"></div>
          <div class="fl w-60 lh-copy pl2 pt2">
            <b class="db">aqua</b>
            <code class="f6">#25BDC3</code>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="fl w-100 w-50-m w-25-l mb1">
          <div class="fl w-40 pv4 hl-bg-yellow"></div>
          <div class="fl w-60 lh-copy pl2 pt2">
            <b class="db">yellow</b>
            <code class="f6">#FDC300</code>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="fl w-100 w-50-m w-25-l mb1">
          <div class="fl w-40 pv4 hl-bg-terracotta"></div>
          <div class="fl w-60 lh-copy pl2 pt2">
            <b class="db">terracotta</b>
            <code class="f6">#ED6A5A</code>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="f3">Helper Function - Standard Components</h1>
      <p class="f5 lh-copy sans-serif">Helper functions are used for individual standard components e.g. a link or a button. They're used for a component that should consistently look the same but that may be used in multiple different contexts.</p>
      <p class="f5 lh-copy sans-serif">To use a helper standard component you need to do 3 things:</p>
      <ul class="f5 lh-copy sans-serif">
        <li>Find an existing component in <code>web/views/component_helpers</code> or create/amend your own</li>
        <li>Check your component_helper file is imported in <code>web/views/component_helpers.ex</code></li>
        <li>Call the function in your html where you wish to position your component.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2 class="f3">Links</h2>
      <p class="measure f5 lh-copy sans-serif">Our basic anchor components.</p>

      <div class="br2 ba bw2 dark-gray b--black-10 pa3 mv4">
        <%= link_to("Link", to: coping_strategy_path(@conn, :new)) %>
      </div>

      <h2 class="f3">Buttons</h1>
      <p class="measure f5 lh-copy sans-serif">Used to create a styled <code>&lt;a&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;button&gt;</code>, or <code>&lt;input&gt;</code> element.</p>

      <div class="br2 ba bw2 dark-gray b--black-10 pa3 mv4">
        <%= link_primary("Primary", to: "#somewhere") %>
        <%= link_secondary("Secondary", to: "#") %>
        <%= link_inactive("Inactive", to: "#") %>

        <%#= button("Button", to: "#", class: primary_classes) %>
      </div>

      <h2 class="f3 mt6 pt4">Partials - Standard Components</h1>
      <p class="measure f5 lh-copy sans-serif">Partials are small templates.
        They are used to contain a collection of elements that always used together.
        Partials can contain helper standard components.</p>


    </div>
  </div>
</section>

